-Good. Good. Come on, kid. Get up.

433
00:27:49,902 --> 00:27:51,422
What the--?

434
00:27:53,038 --> 00:27:54,908
Yeah, I think I got a concussion.

435
00:27:58,710 --> 00:28:01,550
You should meet my brother, Glen.
You guys would really hit it off.

436
00:28:02,114 --> 00:28:06,944
Oh, no. No. Where's my necklace?
Did you see my necklace? It's gotta--

437
00:28:08,420 --> 00:28:09,620
No, no.

438
00:28:09,955 --> 00:28:12,705
Big deal. Get yourself another one
at Reggie's trinket shops.

439
00:28:13,292 --> 00:28:16,101
It's not just some necklace, guy.
He gave it to me himself.

440
00:28:16,662 --> 00:28:19,532
-Who?
-Big Z. When he came to Shiverpool.

441
00:28:20,098 --> 00:28:22,238
That guy believed in me
when no one else did.

442
00:28:22,701 --> 00:28:24,431
He told me never to give up
and to find a way...

443
00:28:24,836 --> 00:28:27,006
-...because that's what winners do.
-What winners do. Yeah.

444
00:28:27,472 --> 00:28:29,722
It's funny, you know,
what a loser I became.

445
00:28:30,209 --> 00:28:33,989
Who cares what Big Z said?
You got to...

446
00:28:35,647 --> 00:28:39,746
-... you know, do things your own way.
-l don't have a way.

447
00:28:42,187 --> 00:28:47,137
You do now. Just follow this.
It'll take you back to North Beach.

448
00:28:48,327 --> 00:28:50,847
Okay, nice to meet you.
Good luck.

449
00:29:00,072 --> 00:29:01,032
What do I do now?

450
00:29:01,340 --> 00:29:04,409
I can't show my face on the beach.
I can't go home.

451
00:29:07,279 --> 00:29:10,789
You always visualize where you're
gonna be, what you're gonna do.

452
00:29:14,987 --> 00:29:16,567
This ain't it.

453
00:29:45,384 --> 00:29:47,964
-What are you doing here?
-Here.

454
00:29:48,487 --> 00:29:51,917
-Oh, man. Thank you, man. This--
-Yeah.

