00:29:52,557 --> 00:29:53,957
That's cool of you to come back.

456
00:29:54,326 --> 00:29:56,106
-Thank you.
-Better keep that knot tight.

457
00:29:56,528 --> 00:29:58,428
You lose it during a contest,
it's a goner.

458
00:29:58,864 --> 00:30:02,024
Yeah, well, I'm not going
in any surf contests.

459
00:30:03,068 --> 00:30:07,898
Well, there's more to surfing
than beating Tank Evans, you know.

460
00:30:09,975 --> 00:30:11,115
Yeah.

461
00:30:11,476 --> 00:30:14,026
Look at that.
You know what you're sitting on there?

462
00:30:15,080 --> 00:30:16,629
That's koa wood.

463
00:30:17,015 --> 00:30:18,885
Best surfboards in the world
are made of that stuff.

464
00:30:19,318 --> 00:30:21,978
-Yeah?
-You got a koa board?

465
00:30:22,521 --> 00:30:27,591
-No, I don't have a "board" board.
-Well, you wanna...?

466
00:30:29,027 --> 00:30:30,367
You want to make one?

467
00:30:31,697 --> 00:30:33,036
-Nah.
-What?

468
00:30:33,398 --> 00:30:35,418
I come all the way back here
to give you the necklace...

469
00:30:35,867 --> 00:30:38,937
..and I'm offering to make you
a board and you say, "Nah."

470
00:30:39,538 --> 00:30:41,938
Get off your lazy butt.
We're making a board. Come on.

471
00:30:42,441 --> 00:30:44,081
-All right.
-It's gonna be the best board...

472
00:30:44,476 --> 00:30:45,376
..you ever had.

473
00:30:45,677 --> 00:30:47,046
-All right?
-Okay, man.

474
00:30:47,412 --> 00:30:48,342
Cody!

475
00:30:51,183 --> 00:30:52,143
That's cool.

476
00:30:52,617 --> 00:30:55,137
Joe, can you just tell us
why you're out here looking for Cody?

477
00:30:55,654 --> 00:30:57,734
You know, we've known
each other way back...

478
00:30:58,190 --> 00:31:02,470
.. since, like, yesterday, I think it was.
We got a lot in common.

479
00:31:03,328 --> 00:31:05,138
! never really knew my father either.

480
00:31:11,703 --> 00:31:14,333
Why are you making surfboards
in the middle of the jungle anyway?

481
00:31:14,873 --> 00:31:17,063
I'm just trying to understand.
I don't get it.

482
00:31:17,542 --> 00:31:20,641
Forget the 20 questions.
Let's just get the board made.

483
00:31:21,480 --> 00:31:25,700
Okay, it's just--
Are you a surfer, or do you--?

484
00:31:28,887 --> 00:31:31,547
-Very funny.
-Less talk, more pushing. Come on.

485
00:31:32,524 --> 00:31:34,603
Why are we pushing it?
Why don't we just roll it?

486
00:31:35,727 --> 00:31:36,717
I'm sorry. I didn't mean--

487
00:31:37,028 --> 00:31:40,308
I didn't know your foot was there.
Are you okay? I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

488
00:31:40,932 --> 00:31:43,592
It's not like I intentionally did it.
I'm sorry.

489
00:31:46,004 --> 00:31:47,964
-Cody. The log!
-Yeah, I know!

490
00:31:49,875 --> 00:31:52,155
Geek! Stop, stop!

491
00:31:53,945 --> 00:31:57,225
Cody, grab the vine. Grab the vine!

492
00:31:59,317 --> 00:32:01,277
-Now, pull it.
-I'm trying!

493
00:32:01,720 --> 00:32:03,300
Pull!

494
00:32:08,160 --> 00:32:09,360
Cody!

495
00:32:10,796 --> 00:32:11,966
Geek!

496
00:32:12,831 --> 00:32:13,940
Cody!

497
00:32:20,505 --> 00:32:23,055
Oh, no, no, no.

498
00:32:25,877 --> 00:32:28,277
Help me up so I can kick your butt.

499
00:32:29,948 --> 00:32:33,818
-l thought I killed you. You okay?
-Next time, when I say don't roll the--

500
00:32:34,519 --> 00:32:36,389
Wait. What's that?

501
00:32:39,357 --> 00:32:42,837
Yeah, it's a beach.
Sand, water, sun.

502
00:32:43,528 --> 00:32:45,838
You seen one, you seen them all.
Let's get out of here.

503
00:32:46,331 --> 00:32:48,321
No, come on, man.
Let's go check it out.

504
00:32:53,839 --> 00:32:55,649
You think Cody and the Geek
are doing all right?

505
00:32:56,074 --> 00:32:58,474
Yeah. I hate to see him
living out there all alone.

506
00:32:58,977 --> 00:33:00,617
It'll be good for him
to have something to do.

507
00:33:13,525 --> 00:33:16,075
Hey. Somebody's old board shack.

508
00:33:24,069 --> 00:33:25,149
Look at this.

509
00:33:29,174 --> 00:33:30,874
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

510
00:33:31,977 --> 00:33:33,937
These are Big Z's boards.

511
00:33:34,379 --> 00:33:38,039
Yeah, these are Big Z's boards.
He rode this in the Australian Open.

512
00:33:39,951 --> 00:33:42,561
This is the board he rode
when he came to Shiverpool, man.

513
00:33:43,088 --> 00:33:45,518
This-- I-- Geek!

514
00:33:46,024 --> 00:33:48,303
This is Big Z's place, man!
This is where he lived!

515
00:33:48,793 --> 00:33:50,283
This is where he made his boards!

516
00:33:50,662 --> 00:33:51,862
Did you know this was here?

517
00:33:52,664 --> 00:33:54,094
Why didn't you wanna
come down here?

518
00:33:54,466 --> 00:33:58,065
And then he went up to this
old shack, you know.

519
00:34:12,484 --> 00:34:15,554
And I realized, you know...

520
00:34:16,987 --> 00:34:18,658
it was Z.

521
00:34:42,147 --> 00:34:45,217
I could tell he needed some space
and some time to himself.

522
00:34:45,951 --> 00:34:47,591
I didn't want to ask him
all these questions.

523
00:34:47,985 --> 00:34:50,415
So I just kind of stood there quietly.

524
00:34:50,922 --> 00:34:53,092
You're Big Z! I can't believe it.

525
00:34:53,558 --> 00:34:55,108
You're alive! You're alive!

526
00:34:55,493 --> 00:34:57,072
That's the respectful way to go,
I think.

527
00:34:57,596 --> 00:34:58,736
Why are you alive?
What happened?

528
00:34:59,064 --> 00:35:01,053
Tell me everything.
Start at the beginning and just go.

529
00:35:01,600 --> 00:35:03,940
Kid! You're gonna
hurt yourself. Relax.

530
00:35:04,436 --> 00:35:07,746
And people said you were dead,
but you're not dead. You're in hiding.

531
00:35:08,540 --> 00:35:09,970
Did something happen?
Something happened.

532
00:35:10,342 --> 00:35:12,362
You saw something
you weren't supposed to see.

533
00:35:12,811 --> 00:35:13,891
I knew it!
That's what happened!

534
00:35:14,212 --> 00:35:16,702
Are you nuts?
It's not a conspiracy. It's no big deal.

535
00:35:17,215 --> 00:35:20,405
-What happened?
-l don't want to talk about it.

536
00:35:23,588 --> 00:35:24,898
You don't-- Okay, I got it!

537
00:35:25,256 --> 00:35:29,326
I'll be over here if you need anything
or you just feel like talking.

538
00:35:30,295 --> 00:35:32,345
Do you feel it now? Like talking now?

539
00:35:32,797 --> 00:35:35,197
-Go away.
-Got it. All right. I'm going away.

540
00:35:35,700 --> 00:35:36,779
Unless you--

541
00:35:37,135 --> 00:35:38,425
-Cody!
-Okay, got it.

542
00:35:38,770 --> 00:35:41,670
I'm not gonna lie to you.
This is, like, it's huge, man.

543
00:35:42,240 --> 00:35:45,200
It changes everything.
The contest is a few days away.

544
00:35:45,777 --> 00:35:50,257
If l can get him to train me, then--
Boom. I could win this with him.

545
00:35:51,349 --> 00:35:54,389
It's my dream. And I don't want to
give up on that dream.

546
00:35:54,986 --> 00:35:57,566
Winners find a way,
no matter what, right?

547
00:35:59,858 --> 00:36:01,728
A winner is....

548
00:36:04,362 --> 00:36:06,202
They see their goals.
They just go for it.

549
00:36:06,631 --> 00:36:08,471
They're not in it
for the money or glory.

550
00:36:08,900 --> 00:36:11,830
-A winner is...like....
-Hey, hey!

551
00:36:13,038 --> 00:36:14,998
It's the surfer who's out there
having the most fun.

552
00:36:15,440 --> 00:36:16,610
Yep, it's a lot of fun.

553
00:36:17,776 --> 00:36:19,995
Right, I get you. What's winning
without the losers?

554
00:36:20,478 --> 00:36:22,648
They're in it for the joy of it
and the rapture...

555
00:36:23,114 --> 00:36:24,864
..and the slow-motion
instant replay, which is my--

556
00:36:25,283 --> 00:36:27,772
Head over to the snack bar
and get yourself a big bowl of shut up!

557
00:36:28,286 --> 00:36:30,716
Feels better when there's a lot
of losers around.

558
00:36:31,222 --> 00:36:32,532
Was that your question?

559
00:36:32,891 --> 00:36:36,701
A winner is somebody who doesn't
knock me off my surfboard...

560
00:36:37,562 --> 00:36:40,082
..and break it when I'm trying
to get some big waves.

561
00:36:40,598 --> 00:36:43,058
Especially Tank.
He is definitely not a winner.

562
00:36:43,568 --> 00:36:46,058
He's a dirty trashcan full of poop.

563
00:36:47,005 --> 00:36:49,255
Yeah, I can't remember a time
when I wasn't surfing.

564
00:36:49,974 --> 00:36:52,344
My mom put me right on there.
I think she pooped me out...

565
00:36:52,844 --> 00:36:53,984
.. Just put me right on there.

566
00:36:54,312 --> 00:36:55,801
What is it about surfing
that you love?

567
00:36:56,281 --> 00:36:58,181
I love being the center of attention...

568
00:36:58,616 --> 00:37:01,016
. . because it's really
where I should be.

569
00:37:01,820 --> 00:37:05,600
And I love the looks
my ladies give me, you know?

570
00:37:06,324 --> 00:37:09,834
The little glint. I love that.
I love holding the ladies.

571
00:37:10,895 --> 00:37:13,205
-You know what I'm talking about?
-I think so.

572
00:37:13,698 --> 00:37:15,808
-Sort of.
-Come with me.

573
00:37:19,270 --> 00:37:20,940
Put this curtain in myself.

574
00:37:23,341 --> 00:37:24,921
These are my ladies.

575
00:37:26,511 --> 00:37:28,651
This is Jill.
This is my lady, Amy.

576
00:37:29,114 --> 00:37:31,164
Little Suzie. Briana.

577
00:37:31,616 --> 00:37:34,196
-You know why we call her Briana?
-No.

578
00:37:34,719 --> 00:37:35,979
It's a long story.

579
00:37:36,321 --> 00:37:38,781
Shaniqua. Helga. Miss Kitty.

580
00:37:39,290 --> 00:37:41,190
Jeannie. I dream of....

581
00:37:41,860 --> 00:37:45,050
Theresa.
This is Theresa right here.

582
00:37:46,164 --> 00:37:49,094
-Now, is Theresa, is that your--
-Dirty girl.

583
00:37:50,101 --> 00:37:54,411
This spot?
This spot is for my special lady, Lia.

584
00:37:55,840 --> 00:37:59,560
I'm gonna say that one more time.
Lia. Oh, yeah.

585
00:38:00,779 --> 00:38:02,119
That's a sweet, sweet lady.

586
00:38:02,514 --> 00:38:04,854
Tank! Are you polishing
your trophies again?

587
00:38:06,651 --> 00:38:10,461
Mom, I wasn't polishing.
l was talking to my friends.

588
00:38:12,590 --> 00:38:14,140
I'm gonna be polishing later.

589
00:38:15,360 --> 00:38:17,700
When's he coming out?
I'm running out of film.

590
00:38:18,863 --> 00:38:21,173
Mr. Topanga! Could you
tell us why you're not dead?

591
00:38:21,666 --> 00:38:24,566
No! lam dead! I'm dead.

592
00:38:30,542 --> 00:38:32,152
What are you doing?

593
00:38:33,945 --> 00:38:35,555
Hey, who said you--

594
00:38:35,947 --> 00:38:38,287
Turn the board around.
Get back here.

595
00:38:38,783 --> 00:38:40,593
Come out here
and show me some moves.

596
00:38:41,052 --> 00:38:42,222
-No, no.
-Come on!

597
00:38:42,554 --> 00:38:45,774
-Grab a board and come out.
-You want to kill yourself, go ahead.

598
00:38:46,391 --> 00:38:48,411
Fine with me.
Just don't mess up my board.

599
00:38:48,860 --> 00:38:52,170
-How do you turn this thing?
-It's not a short board. Sit back on it.

600
00:38:52,797 --> 00:38:54,107
Hey, watch the wave!

601
00:38:56,634 --> 00:38:59,534
You mess up my board,
I'm messing up your other foot.

602
00:39:00,104 --> 00:39:03,823
I'm just trying to ride
this canoe or whatever it is, okay?

603
00:39:04,509 --> 00:39:07,609
Stop trying so hard! Just relax.

604
00:39:08,379 --> 00:39:10,308
What do you mean, rela--?

605
00:39:12,584 --> 00:39:15,044
Long, smooth strokes.

606
00:39:15,553 --> 00:39:18,163
-Dig deep. Dig, come on.
-I'm digging!

607
00:39:18,690 --> 00:39:21,790
Keep the nose up! Keep it up!
Watch it! You're pearling!

608
00:39:28,566 --> 00:39:31,375
-What are you doing?
-Come on, please?

609
00:39:31,936 --> 00:39:34,106
Z, l can't learn anything
with you on the beach.

610
00:39:34,572 --> 00:39:37,092
Well, then you're not gonna
learn anything.

611
00:39:37,609 --> 00:39:40,389
-Now, come on in.
-I'm not coming in until you come out.

612
00:39:40,945 --> 00:39:44,285
Oh, you're coming in, all right.
He's not even watching the wave.

613
00:39:45,049 --> 00:39:46,949
-What wave?
-That one.

614
00:39:47,385 --> 00:39:51,165
Five, four, three, two, and....

615
00:40:03,968 --> 00:40:06,397
-Don't touch my stuff, man.
-l couldn't help it.

616
00:40:06,905 --> 00:40:10,565
-I just wanted to learn from the best.
-Yeah, well.

617
00:40:11,242 --> 00:40:13,522
-l don't surf anymore, okay?
-What?

618
00:40:14,012 --> 00:40:15,442
What do you mean, you don't surf?

619
00:40:15,813 --> 00:40:17,863
You want to learn
how to surf the right way?

620
00:40:18,316 --> 00:40:19,576
Sure.

621
00:40:19,918 --> 00:40:22,408
Then you gotta make
your own board, all right?

622
00:40:23,821 --> 00:40:26,250
-What do you mean, you don't sur--
-Can't hear you.

623
00:40:26,758 --> 00:40:28,368
-Can I ask one question--
-We're making a board.

624
00:40:28,760 --> 00:40:30,950
Could you tell me
about your board?

625
00:40:31,429 --> 00:40:34,619
I just have a palm tree board.

626
00:40:35,500 --> 00:40:37,990
I would have to say it's not
the nicest board in the world...

627
00:40:38,503 --> 00:40:40,203
..but it is a pretty good board.

628
00:40:40,605 --> 00:40:43,065
The ancient Hawaiians believe
that "mana" or heart...

629
00:40:43,574 --> 00:40:46,034
..Was transferred into the surfboard
as you shaped it.

630
00:40:46,544 --> 00:40:48,413
What are your thoughts on that?

631
00:40:48,846 --> 00:40:51,746
What's up with the hair?
You could fit a whole fish in there.

632
00:40:52,317 --> 00:40:54,537
My dream surfboard.
It's pretty powerful.

633
00:40:55,019 --> 00:40:57,948
You can add a lot of attachments to it,
like a grenade launcher attachment.

634
00:40:58,523 --> 00:40:59,663
Anybody know whose board this is?

635
00:40:59,991 --> 00:41:02,511
-I'm pretty sure it's the chicken's.
-Has anybody seen the chicken?

636
00:41:03,027 --> 00:41:04,837
Cody!

637
00:41:05,396 --> 00:41:08,676
I know he's out here.
Il can feel it in my nuggets.

638
00:41:09,300 --> 00:41:12,320
Aren't you nervous out here
in the jungle? It's kind of dangerous.

639
00:41:12,904 --> 00:41:16,064
Dude, the jungle is the most
peaceful place on the planet.

640
00:41:22,380 --> 00:41:25,190
-Hold it steady.
-This is a dream come true.

641
00:41:25,750 --> 00:41:28,500
This is a dream come true,
to be here with Z, doing this.

642
00:41:29,053 --> 00:41:30,803
-And it's koa wood.
-Where's the--

643
00:41:31,222 --> 00:41:32,952
All the best boards
are made from koa wood.

644
00:41:33,725 --> 00:41:37,825
All right, now,
I drew this pattern as a guide.

645
00:41:38,563 --> 00:41:42,723
Do you want to have your board
with a lot of rocker or just a little?

646
00:41:44,035 --> 00:41:45,205
I don't know.

647
00:41:45,536 --> 00:41:48,196
What you want is something
in-between. Trust me.

648
00:41:48,740 --> 00:41:50,140
-I'm the expert here.
-Okay.

649
00:41:50,942 --> 00:41:52,052
So...

650
00:41:52,577 --> 00:41:54,447
.. here are your shaping tools.

651
00:41:55,146 --> 00:41:59,366
Now, remember, the board's
already inside there, see, somewhere.

652
00:42:00,118 --> 00:42:03,048
And what you're doing
is you're trying to find it.

653
00:42:03,621 --> 00:42:05,961
-Reveal it. All right?
-Okay.

654
00:42:06,724 --> 00:42:09,744
Every carve counts.
Why are you smiling? Don't smile.

655
00:42:10,328 --> 00:42:13,838
-I'm not smiling. I'm excited.
-This isn't like hacking a piece of ice.

656
00:42:14,499 --> 00:42:16,609
It takes patience and finesse.

657
00:42:17,068 --> 00:42:19,938
All right already. Can you just
give me the tools, please?

658
00:42:20,505 --> 00:42:22,755
-Here, take it. Go ahead.
-Thank you.

659
00:42:24,008 --> 00:42:26,638
-Here we go.
-What are you doing?

660
00:42:28,346 --> 00:42:30,156
If you're gonna do it, do it right.

661
00:42:30,581 --> 00:42:33,361
All right, look.
First of all, with the grain.

662
00:42:33,985 --> 00:42:36,645
With the grain.
You see what I'm doing here?

663
00:42:37,255 --> 00:42:40,565
You let the tool do the work.
You see?

664
00:42:41,192 --> 00:42:43,682
Just like you're riding a wave.
You let the wave do the work.

665
00:42:44,195 --> 00:42:47,885
You don't fight the wave.
You can't fight these big waves.

666
00:42:48,566 --> 00:42:52,316
Long strokes. Loads of finesse.

667
00:42:53,805 --> 00:42:56,555
Find the board within the tree.

668
00:42:57,108 --> 00:42:59,828
-Nice and easy.
-Yeah, I got it.

669
00:43:00,378 --> 00:43:02,278
See that? You just...

670
00:43:03,047 --> 00:43:04,797
-You just...
-Maybe I could do it now.

671
00:43:05,216 --> 00:43:06,616
Move with...

672
00:43:07,819 --> 00:43:10,069
-With the...
-Can I do it now?

673
00:43:12,190 --> 00:43:13,560
Can I do it now?

674
00:43:16,828 --> 00:43:19,898
Yeah. I got carried away.
Sorry about that.

675
00:43:20,498 --> 00:43:22,278
-It's your board.
-My board.

676
00:43:23,468 --> 00:43:24,808
Okay, with the grain. I got it.

677
00:43:25,169 --> 00:43:27,129
Don't forget to eyeball it
once in a while.

678
00:43:27,572 --> 00:43:30,792
-Long strokes, with the grain.
-Not too long.

679
00:43:31,409 --> 00:43:32,989
Here we go.

680
00:43:37,181 --> 00:43:39,291
-You're doing it wrong.
-Will you just let me--

681
00:43:39,750 --> 00:43:42,590
I can't-- No finesse
when you're in my face. Okay?

682
00:43:43,154 --> 00:43:44,854
Just let me make the board.

683
00:43:45,256 --> 00:43:47,656
-Do you want my help?
-No, I don't want your help.

684
00:43:48,159 --> 00:43:49,329
I don't want your help.

685
00:43:49,660 --> 00:43:51,390
-You don't want my help?
-[ don't want your help.

686
00:43:51,796 --> 00:43:54,486
-All right. Fine.
-l want to make my board.

687
00:43:55,032 --> 00:43:58,162
-Build the board yourself, all right?
-Thank you.

688
00:43:58,769 --> 00:44:01,669
