01:02:49,833 --> 01:02:50,853
-Cody!
-Joe!

931
01:02:51,401 --> 01:02:54,301
-I've been looking everywhere for you!
-You've been looking for me?

932
01:02:54,871 --> 01:02:57,361
I didn't lose you on the whale.
I'm not gonna lose you now.

933
01:02:57,874 --> 01:03:00,894
-Thank you. Seriously, thank you.
-Radical.

934
01:03:03,546 --> 01:03:05,716
They're starting!
Cody, we gotta go! Come on!

935
01:03:06,216 --> 01:03:07,506
Wait a minute. Joe?

936
01:03:07,851 --> 01:03:08,811
Surfers riding....

937
01:03:09,119 --> 01:03:11,779
I'm sorry. Watch this, dude.
Il can speak their language.

938
01:03:16,059 --> 01:03:18,869
I totally need my board. I don't
know where it is. gotta go find it.

939
01:03:19,429 --> 01:03:21,359
-I'll see you in the lineup.
-See you, Joe.

940
01:03:21,798 --> 01:03:24,017
-This is gonna be fun, huh?
-See you.

941
01:03:25,935 --> 01:03:29,185
The tenth annual Big Z
is about to get underway...

942
01:03:29,806 --> 01:03:32,266
..and, whoa, it is the day of days.

943
01:03:32,776 --> 01:03:35,586
Big mountainous bombs
marching into our coastline.

944
01:03:36,279 --> 01:03:39,469
Kelly Slater, on a danger level,
one to ten, give me a number.

945
01:03:40,083 --> 01:03:40,953
Twenty.

946
01:03:41,251 --> 01:03:43,031
-Wow. Rob?
-There'll be blood.

947
01:03:43,453 --> 01:03:45,153
I'm scared, and I'm in the booth!

948
01:03:46,356 --> 01:03:48,256
-What are you doing here?
-Mike.

949
01:03:48,692 --> 01:03:50,682
You're gonna kill yourself.
Don't do this to yourself.

950
01:03:51,127 --> 01:03:52,297
Look what happened last time.

951
01:03:53,163 --> 01:03:55,153
-It's good to see you back.
-Are you serious?

952
01:03:55,598 --> 01:03:56,938
You're gonna be
a real crowd pleaser.

953
01:03:57,300 --> 01:03:59,350
I'm telling you,
these people are gonna eat you up.

954
01:03:59,803 --> 01:04:02,873
-I'll be expecting big things from you.
-Thank you.

955
01:04:03,473 --> 01:04:05,433
People, big announcement.
Cody Maverick, he's back.

956
01:04:05,875 --> 01:04:07,045
The Wipeout King is back...

957
01:04:07,377 --> 01:04:09,217
..and I'm gonna tell you,
start looking for the sharks.

958
01:04:09,646 --> 01:04:11,456
They'll be circling because
there's gonna be blood.

959
01:04:11,881 --> 01:04:13,141
Spectacular carnage today.

960
01:04:13,483 --> 01:04:16,943
Thank you! Reggie Belafonte. Little
guy, big hair, big thoughts, big heart.

961
01:04:26,296 --> 01:04:29,776
Look at this.
You're going down, snowflake.

962
01:04:31,434 --> 01:04:34,274
I'm gonna make you wish
you were never even hatched.

963
01:04:35,805 --> 01:04:38,024
You want to see my trophies?

964
01:04:47,951 --> 01:04:49,561
Arnold, no.

965
01:04:55,792 --> 01:04:58,422
About 24 surfers
battling their way out to the--

966
01:04:59,829 --> 01:05:02,289
Good golly! Make that 18.

967
01:05:05,902 --> 01:05:08,012
Rob, after such a heavy wipeout
earlier in the week...

968
01:05:08,471 --> 01:05:10,251
...what do you think is going
through Maverick's mind?

969
01:05:10,673 --> 01:05:14,183
He's gonna have to stay focused and
channel that energy into good places.

970
01:05:14,978 --> 01:05:16,438
When are you gonna get a life?

971
01:05:19,048 --> 01:05:20,598
You are a nobody.

972
01:05:22,085 --> 01:05:24,045
You should've stayed
in Antarctica, kid.

973
01:05:48,878 --> 01:05:51,398
He made it! Yeah, good.

974
01:05:51,915 --> 01:05:55,315
What an amazing first ride
mind-blower from Maverick.

975
01:06:01,491 --> 01:06:02,951
Did you guys see that?

976
01:06:03,326 --> 01:06:06,046
Man. I thought I was gonna lose it,
and then I just...

977
01:06:07,664 --> 01:06:10,214
I just let go, you know.
I let go, and there it was.

978
01:06:11,835 --> 01:06:14,175
Wow, it's been an amazing day...

979
01:06:14,671 --> 01:06:16,421
...0f shredding in less than
stellar conditions...

980
01:06:16,840 --> 01:06:19,420
..but 1 never would have guessed
our three finalists.

981
01:06:19,943 --> 01:06:21,813
Well, Sal, it's no surprise
that Tank Evans...

982
01:06:22,245 --> 01:06:24,964
..has just breezed his way
into the finals.

983
01:06:25,515 --> 01:06:29,295
And Cody Maverick, from a horrible
wipeout a few days ago to this.

984
01:06:32,188 --> 01:06:35,028
And Chicken Joe from Sheboygan.
Who would have guessed it?

985
01:06:36,059 --> 01:06:38,959
! have never seen a finals like this.

986
01:06:40,497 --> 01:06:42,807
-We're in the finals, Joe.
-No way! We get to surf some more?

987
01:06:43,299 --> 01:06:46,229
Isn't it exciting?
Look at that. This is great, huh?

988
01:06:46,903 --> 01:06:49,832
You know, you should know this.
The Tank loves you.

989
01:06:51,140 --> 01:06:53,279
Looks like this will be
the easiest year ever.

990
01:06:54,644 --> 01:06:57,303
No way. Cody, did you hear that?
It's gonna be easy.

991
01:06:58,414 --> 01:07:00,754
Are you loving this?

992
01:07:03,486 --> 01:07:05,185
So who would you like
to see win the trophy?

993
01:07:05,588 --> 01:07:07,868
It's not so important to me.

994
01:07:08,358 --> 01:07:10,698
Friends are better than anything
in the world.

995
01:07:11,194 --> 01:07:12,244
Friends are forever.

996
01:07:13,029 --> 01:07:15,929
Trophies, you never know
what they can have happen to them.

997
01:07:17,600 --> 01:07:20,089
-That was awesome, mate.
-Muy impresivo, my friend.

998
01:07:20,603 --> 01:07:21,773
Thank you, bro. Thanks.

999
01:07:22,705 --> 01:07:23,935
-Finals.
-Hey!

1000
01:07:24,274 --> 01:07:26,614
Yeah. I know. I can't even--

1001
01:07:27,877 --> 01:07:30,217
I think I can win this thing.
It's too much right now.

1002
01:07:30,713 --> 01:07:32,903
-Well, that's all you came for.
-What?

1003
01:07:33,383 --> 01:07:36,102
-What is that supposed to mean?
-You made it pretty clear last night...

1004
01:07:36,653 --> 01:07:38,462
.. that winning's more important
to you than Z or me.

1005
01:07:38,888 --> 01:07:40,998
But, hey, maybe you'll get to take
your stupid trophy home.

1006
01:07:41,457 --> 01:07:43,567
-Lani. Come on.
-Come here, you!

1007
01:07:44,327 --> 01:07:45,497
How about this, huh?

1008
01:07:45,828 --> 01:07:50,278
Let me tell you something. You win
this thing, we're going places!

1009
01:07:51,100 --> 01:07:53,650
Look at this kid.
He is a champ!

1010
01:08:03,580 --> 01:08:07,240
Tank, nine-time defending champion.
He will roll on you.

1011
01:08:07,917 --> 01:08:10,987
Expect him to win this thing. It's
basically a contest for second place.

1012
01:08:11,588 --> 01:08:15,688
First, I'm gonna take you down.
Then I'm gonna fry the chicken.

1013
01:08:18,428 --> 01:08:20,978
That cloud looks just like a kitten.

1014
01:08:34,844 --> 01:08:36,424
Maverick and Evans take off.

1015
01:08:37,346 --> 01:08:38,246
Mine!

1016
01:08:38,548 --> 01:08:40,598
And it's Evans dropping in.

1017
01:08:43,653 --> 01:08:46,283
And Tank's playing games,
blocking Maverick's every move.

1018
01:08:47,590 --> 01:08:48,930
Maverick sticks a rail.

1019
01:08:50,326 --> 01:08:54,456
Tank Evans down!
! have never, ever seen this before!

1020
01:08:57,000 --> 01:08:58,310
But I'd love to see it again.

1021
01:08:58,667 --> 01:09:01,857
Cody trying to take back the wave
that Tank snaked from him.

1022
01:09:02,471 --> 01:09:04,492
Evans toying with him,
not paying attention.

1023
01:09:04,941 --> 01:09:06,901
And there's the outside rail.
Evans goes down.

1024
01:09:07,343 --> 01:09:11,322
And it's Maverick with this new-school
move. We'll call it "The Maverick."

1025
01:09:17,687 --> 01:09:20,466
And look at this.
Maverick scoring big.

1026
01:09:21,924 --> 01:09:25,823
Oh, it's so cute.
It's got little paws and the whiskers.

1027
01:09:29,332 --> 01:09:31,822
Chicken Joe
with a no-paddle drop-in!

1028
01:09:33,836 --> 01:09:36,326
-Here we go!
-Nobody needs to help this chicken.

1029
01:09:37,707 --> 01:09:38,787
I'm flying!

1030
01:09:40,810 --> 01:09:45,030
Maverick and Joe tied, and no score
for Tank Evans? Unbelievable.

1031
01:09:47,216 --> 01:09:50,616
Surfers, this is your final wave!

1032
01:09:51,254 --> 01:09:55,064
-Joe, this is it. This wave wins it.
-Yeah, man!

1033
01:09:57,593 --> 01:10:01,403
This wave is stacking up
to be a beautiful tube.

1034
01:10:02,565 --> 01:10:05,405
Maverick should score big
on this one!

1035
01:10:07,637 --> 01:10:09,687
But wait! Evans drops in.

1036
01:10:10,139 --> 01:10:13,299
It looks like Evans
is gonna take out the chicken.

1037
01:10:19,148 --> 01:10:20,318
What's Maverick doing?

1038
01:10:20,650 --> 01:10:23,200
-Go, Joe, go!
-Got it! Let's go!

1039
01:10:23,720 --> 01:10:26,270
! don't believe this.
This contest was Maverick's to win.

1040
01:10:26,823 --> 01:10:30,103
Now Evans pushing Maverick out
of bounds and into The Boneyards.

1041
01:10:43,272 --> 01:10:45,762
-Tank, look out!
-You look out!

1042
01:11:21,477 --> 01:11:22,347
Code!

1043
01:11:25,014 --> 01:11:25,884
Z!

1044
01:11:30,153 --> 01:11:31,823
-Cody, come on.
-Z!}

1045
01:11:32,221 --> 01:11:35,531
Paddle! Come on! Dig! Faster!
Come on. Dig!

1046
01:11:37,226 --> 01:11:39,335
Don't dig! Don't dig!

1047
01:11:39,796 --> 01:11:40,756
What?

1048
01:11:41,564 --> 01:11:43,784
Let the wave carry you!

1049
01:11:44,734 --> 01:11:46,194
You're gonna have to time it!

1050
01:11:46,936 --> 01:11:49,686
You're gonna come right here,
right to me!

1051
01:11:53,609 --> 01:11:55,359
Five...four....

1052
01:11:55,845 --> 01:11:58,125
Three...two...one.

1053
01:12:03,519 --> 01:12:04,809
Z!

1054
01:12:20,269 --> 01:12:21,639
Where's Cody?

1055
01:12:26,209 --> 01:12:28,019
Don't touch it! Don't touch that!

1056
01:12:28,444 --> 01:12:31,164
This is a reminder
of the young surfer...

1057
01:12:31,714 --> 01:12:36,164
..who gave his life
for the sport he loved.

1058
01:12:40,990 --> 01:12:42,570
There you are.

1059
01:12:47,563 --> 01:12:50,463
I can't believe it! 1 can't believe it.

1060
01:12:52,068 --> 01:12:53,238
You came back.

1061
01:12:53,903 --> 01:12:56,243
You saved my life, man.
Thank you.

1062
01:12:56,739 --> 01:12:59,699
Hey, hey, come on.
You're gonna tip us!

1063
01:13:01,944 --> 01:13:04,254
Well, I lost.

1064
01:13:06,249 --> 01:13:07,739
Me too.

1065
01:13:10,086 --> 01:13:12,716
Come on. Let's go, loser.

1066
01:13:13,923 --> 01:13:15,123
You want to help me out here?

1067
01:13:15,458 --> 01:13:19,968
You know the routine. Come on. Long.
That's it. Smooth, you know. Come on.

1068
01:13:20,930 --> 01:13:25,320
Young Joey MacEnroe
was a beacon for a new generation.

1069
01:13:26,102 --> 01:13:28,712
May he rest in peace.

1070
01:13:30,973 --> 01:13:33,663
So, what am I bid for the board?
Who'll give me 30? 30, come on.

1071
01:13:34,210 --> 01:13:36,110
-Don't touch his stuff, man.
-Pal, if you want to bid--

1072
01:13:36,545 --> 01:13:38,475
-Give me that.
-Hey--!

1073
01:13:44,487 --> 01:13:46,007
Hey. Hey, everyone.

1074
01:13:47,223 --> 01:13:49,243
-How you been?
-Oh, my gosh!

1075
01:13:49,725 --> 01:13:51,625
-Yeah...
-Hey, man, that's Z.

1076
01:13:52,094 --> 01:13:53,464
..that's me.

1077
01:13:53,829 --> 01:13:55,789
Skank, what's happening, man?

1078
01:13:56,232 --> 01:13:58,572
Got a little sand
in your egg sac there, fella.

1079
01:13:59,068 --> 01:14:01,118
-Where have you been, Z?
-What happened?

1080
01:14:02,271 --> 01:14:03,441
Oh, you know...

1081
01:14:05,574 --> 01:14:09,964
..1 got lost for a little while.
But that kid there, Cody...

1082
01:14:11,781 --> 01:14:14,271
.. he pointed the way back.

1083
01:14:25,461 --> 01:14:27,391
Could you please shut that off?
Could you give me a minute?

1084
01:14:34,036 --> 01:14:35,736
Check it out! How about this?

1085
01:14:36,138 --> 01:14:38,308
You want to talk about talent scout?
People find talent.

1086
01:14:38,808 --> 01:14:43,788
I bring them back from the dead.
The now living legend, ladies and--

1087
01:14:44,647 --> 01:14:45,817
-Shut up.
-What? Shut up?

1088
01:14:46,148 --> 01:14:49,658
I'm not a legend. I'm a guy looking for
some nice waves, some good friends.

1089
01:14:50,653 --> 01:14:53,843
Hey, guys, the swell is happening
over on the north shore!

1090
01:14:54,457 --> 01:14:55,657
I'm right behind you, Z.

1091
01:14:55,992 --> 01:14:57,162
Ouch, that hurt.

1092
01:14:59,462 --> 01:15:03,212
Come back here!
You don't just walk away! Come on!

1093
01:15:05,101 --> 01:15:06,300
He's taking this loss pretty hard.

1094
01:15:06,635 --> 01:15:09,245
Tank, how does it feel
to lose after nine time--

1095
01:15:11,240 --> 01:15:14,080
l wasn't kissing her.
You can't have her!

1096
01:15:18,014 --> 01:15:18,884
Can we get a few words?

1097
01:15:19,181 --> 01:15:21,521
You gave up the trophy to help Joe.
What's that about?

1098
01:15:22,018 --> 01:15:24,568
You know, Rob,
that's what friends do.

1099
01:15:25,087 --> 01:15:27,837
-How's it feel to win, Joe?
-l won?

1100
01:15:28,391 --> 01:15:31,290
Come on! I'll tell my mom.
Gimme. Gimme!

1101
01:15:33,362 --> 01:15:35,882
Oh, Lia! Oh, Lia.

1102
01:15:36,399 --> 01:15:39,559
Don't you walk away from me!
lam Reggie Belafon--

1103
01:15:41,504 --> 01:15:44,604
Turn that thing off.
Mikey! You are so fired!

1104
01:15:45,641 --> 01:15:47,951
I can't imagine a better day.

1105
01:15:54,450 --> 01:15:57,960
Dude, this-- This whole
experience has just been--

1106
01:15:58,654 --> 01:16:01,204
It's amazing. Z?

1107
01:16:01,724 --> 01:16:06,034
I don't think I've ever had
a better friend to me in my life.

1108
01:16:06,796 --> 01:16:10,016
It's just really cool
to have everything I need.

1109
01:16:11,333 --> 01:16:13,503
-Don't do it. Help!
-Arnold!

1110
01:16:13,969 --> 01:16:16,959
To be honest, man, I'm kind of, like,
bored of talking about myself.

1111
01:16:17,540 --> 01:16:20,760
So, is that cool?
You guys got what you need?

1112
01:16:21,377 --> 01:16:23,397
-We got it
-All right. Be good!

1113
01:16:32,288 --> 01:16:33,628
Cowabunga!

1114
01:17:41,857 --> 01:17:43,557
Of course we're proud of him!

1115
01:17:43,959 --> 01:17:45,568
What mother wouldn't be
proud of him?

1116
01:17:45,961 --> 01:17:47,951
We're so full of proudness.

1117
01:17:48,397 --> 01:17:50,067
You know what?
He followed his dream...

1118
01:17:50,466 --> 01:17:53,776
..and he went out there, and now
he's coming home with the trophy.

1119
01:17:54,403 --> 01:17:56,153
l can't wait to see his trophy.

1120
01:17:56,572 --> 01:17:58,322
There's not really a trophy.

1121
01:17:59,308 --> 01:18:01,448
Is there, like, a big shell
or something like that?

1122
01:18:01,911 --> 01:18:04,311
There's no shell. There's no trophy.
Well, he didn't win.

1123
01:18:04,813 --> 01:18:05,713
What?

1124
01:18:06,215 --> 01:18:08,845
How bad was it?
Did he get smoked?

1125
01:18:09,418 --> 01:18:12,197
-He was in the finals.
-Second place? That's losing.

1126
01:18:12,755 --> 01:18:14,805
-Winning is not everything, Glen.
-Right.

1127
01:18:15,257 --> 01:18:16,567
Look at what Cody did--

1128
01:18:16,926 --> 01:18:18,826
Go back to the
"winning isn't everything" thing.

1129
01:18:19,328 --> 01:18:21,318
That doesn't compute, really.

1130
01:18:21,764 --> 01:18:26,594
You know what, Glen? I really hope
someday you can be more like Cody.

1131
01:18:27,736 --> 01:18:29,026
This interview is over.

1132
01:24:59,861 --> 01:25:01,971
Remember when were talking
about you leaving? That was great.

1133
01:25:02,431 --> 01:25:03,861
Remember when
you were gonna go?

1134
01:25:04,232 --> 01:25:06,012
-We were gonna go--
-You should still go.

1135
01:25:06,501 --> 01:25:07,431
It's technical equipment.

1136
01:25:07,736 --> 01:25:11,246
I know what I'm doing. I can unplug
one of your little Hollywood devices.

1137
01:25:12,240 --> 01:25:14,260
The lighting thing,
whatever you call that...

1138
01:25:14,710 --> 01:25:16,350
..and then the microphone thing.

1139
01:25:16,745 --> 01:25:17,915
Go back to Hollywood.

1140
01:25:18,246 --> 01:25:19,556
Cody would never do this.

